Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the effective signal-to-noise ratio (SNR) and symbol error rate, which are key concepts in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses a cooperative scenario with multiple relays, which is a common topic in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking): The paper deals with communication over fading channels and amplify-and-forward protocol, which are common topics in communication and networking. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the performance of a selection scheme, which can be viewed as a control system. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the capacity per bandwidth of the received signal, which is relevant to multimedia applications.
